    "citation": "Djordjevic 2016 26762380",
    "population": "N: 40 (Serbian) Age: 11 (4-16) WT: 39 (17-65) CYP1A2*1A/*1A: 6 CYP1A2*1A/*1F: 16 CYP1A2*1F/*1F: 18",
    "model_type": "PK",
    "objective": "“to investigate the potential effect of CYP1A2 genetic polymorphisms on carbamazepine pharmacokinetics in children with epilepsy”",
    "covariates": "Tested:AGE, WT, SEX, CBZ daily dose, CYP1A2 polymorphisms, VPA Included: SEX, CBZ daily dose, CYP1A2 polymorphisms on CL",
    "observations": "In CYP1A2*1A/*1A subjects, CL was increased by approximately 11% compared to CYP1A2*1A/*1F and CYP1A2*1F/*1F subjects. WT did not seem to influence CL here",
    "dose": "Steady-state oral doses in patients",
    "structure": "Simplified 1 compartment with no absorption",
    "equations": "CL=(theta1 + theta2*SEX + theta3*CYP1A2 + theta4*DD)*exp(eta1) Although the paper reports the use of ADVAN1, no parameter values for volume were given. As such, the model can only be used as a simplified PK model using the following equation for Css: Css-avg=(Dose*S)/(Tau*CL/F)*exp(eps1) The implementation of an exponential inter-individual variability of CL was assumed here, as it was not reported in the paper what form was finally found to best describe the data DD: daily dose of CBZ in mg/day SEX: gender (female: 0, male: 1) CYP1A2: polymorphisms (0 for *1F/*1F or *1A/*1F; 1 for *1A/*1A)",
    "parameter_values": "theta1=0.176 theta2=0.0484 theta3=0.019 theta4=0.000156 omega1=0.0383 sigma1=0.025",
    "validation": "Yes (bootstrap of 1000)/ No"
  },
